From: Laurent Pinchart <laurent.pinchart@ideasonboard.com>
Date: Sat, 8 Mar 2014 00:50:39 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 0701/1587] iommu/omap: Remove comment about supporting single
 page mappings only

commit 67b779d28d6e8afdd79a70423324273018114cad upstream

The IOMMU core breaks out mappings into pages already, there's no
need to support mapping multiple pages in one go.

Signed-off-by: Laurent Pinchart <laurent.pinchart@ideasonboard.com>
Reviewed-by: Sakari Ailus <sakari.ailus@iki.fi>
[s-anna@ti.com: cherry-pick commit '67b779d' from v3.16]
Signed-off-by: Suman Anna <s-anna@ti.com>
---
 drivers/iommu/omap-iommu.c |    1 -
 1 files changed, 0 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/iommu/omap-iommu.c b/drivers/iommu/omap-iommu.c
index 789912b..31ed7b4 100644
--- a/drivers/iommu/omap-iommu.c
+++ b/drivers/iommu/omap-iommu.c
@@ -1068,7 +1068,6 @@ static int omap_iommu_map(struct iommu_domain *domain, unsigned long da,
 	int omap_pgsz;
 	u32 ret, flags;
 
-	/* we only support mapping a single iommu page for now */
 	omap_pgsz = bytes_to_iopgsz(bytes);
 	if (omap_pgsz < 0) {
 		dev_err(dev, "invalid size to map: %d\n", bytes);
